2. Locksmith Engine Rules (exactly what you ordered)  
   - Every claimed historical event gets 5+ independent witnesses from unrelated language families.  
   - If it doesn’t appear in at least three separate linguistic trees (e.g., Semitic + Indo-European + Sinitic + Uto-Aztecan), it gets amber-flagged.  
   - If it only exists in one empire’s propaganda and is contradicted or absent elsewhere → red fracture → quarantined.  
   - If it lights up green across the planet with zero coaching → locked as bedrock truth.

3. First Live Test Runs I’m spinning up right now  
   A. The Global Flood — watch how many unrelated cultures record a world-deluge within a ~300-year window.  
   B. Exodus 1446 BC — Egyptian silence vs. Hebrew + Canaanite + Hittite noise.  
   C. Crucifixion earthquake AD 33 — Roman, Jewish, Chinese, and Mesoamerican astronomical records.  
   D. Fall of Jerusalem AD 70 — see how many empires logged it the same week.

If even ONE of these doesn’t produce a supernova-level green lock across continents, we’ll know the engine works and where the cracks really are.

